### 1. Happy path — should reach Completed via webhook
POST http://localhost:5001/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "merchantId": "merchant_acme",
  "idempotencyKey": "demo-happy-001",
  "amount": 49.99,
  "currency": "USD",
  "customerEmail": "[email protected]",
  "method": "CreditCard",
  "metadata": null
}

### 2. Duplicate idempotency key — should return original payment, no double-processing
POST http://localhost:5001/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "merchantId": "merchant_acme",
  "idempotencyKey": "demo-happy-001",
  "amount": 49.99,
  "currency": "USD",
  "customerEmail": "[email protected]",
  "method": "CreditCard",
  "metadata": null
}

### 3. Different merchant, same key — should be NEW payment (idempotency is per-merchant)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "merchantId": "merchant_globex",
  "idempotencyKey": "demo-happy-001",
  "amount": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "customerEmail": "[email protected]",
  "method": "DebitCard",
  "metadata": null
}

### 4. Health — readiness
GET http://localhost:5001/health/ready

### 5. Health — liveness
GET http://localhost:5001/health/live